<plot>Performed exclusively in American Sign Language and created by a collaborative team of deaf and hearing artists. Based on the short story by Pulitzer Prize-winner Eudora Welty. Like many of Welty's stories, THE KEY is set among people from the poor, rural South and explores the depths and limits of human communication.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?568047</url></doc>
